mp_definition: any structural anomaly of the hollow epithelial tube found on the dorsal side of the vertebrate embryo that develops into the central nervous system (i.e. brain and spinal cord)
arrest of the axial rotation of the germ layers of the embryo during the primitive streak/early somite stage
aberrant or incomplete differentiation of the brain
malformation or arrest of differentiation of the visual organ
larger than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls
increased or decreased average body size, weight or growth characteristic abnormalities manifesting after birth
anomaly in the establishment of the characteristic configuration of the embryonic body
any structural anomaly of the fibroserous membrane covering the heart and beginning of the great vessels
deviation from the normal function of the immune system

any anomaly in the reflexive action mediated by cells of the spinal cord, or the involuntary movement reaction caused by the application of a stimulus to an organism; these include signals originating from heat from burning, sharp sensations, and other painful feelings
any structural anomaly of the spheroid organ and optic nerve that serves to detect light
smaller than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls
any structural anomaly of any of the structures involved in the ear or vestibular system
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of calcium ions within the body or between a cell and its external environment
any anomaly in the development and invagination of the embryonic germ layers

any structural anomaly of the extensive, intricate network of electochemical structures in the body that is comprised of the brain, spinal cord, nerves, ganglia and parts of the receptor organs that receive and interpret stimuli and transmit impulses to effector organs to control body functions
any functional anomaly in the ability to perceive auditory stimuli
any structural anomaly of the hollow, muscular organ that maintains the circulation of the blood
aberrant formation or incomplete differentiation of the heart
any anomaly in the concentration in the blood of the enzyme which hydrolyzes orthophosphoric monoesters; low levels are seen in cases of hypophosphatasia
anomaly in the process in which parasympathetic nerves stimulate the bladder wall muscle to contract resulting in the expulsion of urine from the body

atypical axial rotation of the germ layers of the embryo during the primitive streak/early somite stage during which the curvature of the entire trunk region is normally reversed and the neural ectoderm moves to the convex region and the midgut region becomes located in the concave region
